ilm and digital media. The essays draw upon a variety of voices, spanning various religious and ethnic communities, including Hindus, Muslims, Jains, Parsees and Siddhi Africans, and caste identities, such as that of the bard, ballad singer, king, priest, court chronicler, soldier, mason and drummer.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 3.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 7aHISTORY / Asia / India & South Asia.2bisacsh  aDynastic history, elites, etnohistory, Gujarat, Halvad-Dhrangadhra, Indian kingdoms, Jhala court, Jhala dynasty, Jhalavad, Kshatriya, Kuva-no-ker, miniature paintings, Rajput, Rani Jijima, western India.1 aJhala, Angma D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJhala, Jayasinji, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcClenaghan, Tony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcGrath, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcLeod, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOppenheim, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Packagez978311064982608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSciendo All Ebooks Trial Collection 2024z97831115024960 cEPUBz97831106056620 cprintz978311060128240uhttps://sciendo.com/book/9783110601299zOpen Access70  a978-3-11-064982-6 Asian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Package  a978-3-11-150249-6 Sciendo All Ebooks Trial Collection 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA